Cluster module allows creating multiple Node.js processes to utilize multi-core CPUs.

**Basic Cluster Setup**:
```javascript
const cluster = require('cluster');
const numCPUs = require('os').cpus().length;

if (cluster.isMaster) {
  console.log(`Master ${process.pid} is running`);

  // Fork workers
  for (let i = 0; i < numCPUs; i++) {
    cluster.fork();
  }

  cluster.on('exit', (worker, code, signal) => {
    console.log(`Worker ${worker.process.pid} died`);
    cluster.fork(); // Restart worker
  });
} else {
  // Worker processes
  console.log(`Worker ${process.pid} started`);
  // Start your server here
}
```

**Worker Communication**:
```javascript
// Master to worker
worker.send({ message: 'Hello worker' });

// Worker to master
process.send({ message: 'Hello master' });
```

**Benefits**:
- Utilizes all CPU cores
- Improved performance
- Automatic worker restart
- Load distribution

Cluster enables Node.js applications to scale across CPU cores!

